title: 820-4924 power but no boot with trackpad plugged in
message: 820-4924 liquid damage, C5125 and R5489 were corroded so I replaced them and it turns on now, however once I plug the trackpad in it chimes then gets stuck at a blank black screen before the Apple logo. Already tried a known good trackpad and cable, and the trackpad does click when it is on. Ideas?

title: 820-4924 power but no boot with trackpad plugged in
message: Disconnect keyboard and try again. Checked J4802 for corrosion?
